erver exits with its session; PPID-1 orphan reap | Complete |\n117: | 007 | `007-ipc-client-cap-hardening/` | Daemon IPC client cap raised 8 to 64 across sources and nine config env blocks | Complete |\n118: \n119: ### Phase Transition Rules\n120: \n121: - Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins.\n122: - Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map.\n123: - Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase.\n124: - Run `validate.sh --recursive` on the parent to validate all phases as an integrated unit.\n125: \n126: ### Phase Handoff Criteria\n127: \n128: | From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n129: |------|----|----------|--------------|\n130: | (per-child) | (next child) | Each child ships and validates independently under tolerant policy | Per-child strict validation evidence |\n131: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n136: ## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS\n137: \n138: - None open at the parent level; per-phase questions live in the child folders.\n139: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n144: \n145: - **Phase children**: See sub-folders `[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/` for per-phase spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md.\n146: - **Parent Spec**: See `../spec.md`.\n147: - **Graph Metadata**: See `graph-metadata.json` for `derived.last_active_child_id` pointer.\n\n(End of file - total 147 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| child phase folders `[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/` | Modify/Create | all | Per-phase implementation lives in the child folders |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 001 | `001-mcp-to-cli-tool-transition/` | Dual-stack CLI front-doo