{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781422970912,"sessionID":"ses_13aef63ccffel7tpaI1Dzxs3uq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ae669a733c7a4d468911d58c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md","limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Chronological Timeline [system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline]\"\n3: description: \"GENERATED chronological index of 027 live-tree spec folders, newest to oldest by git activity. The recency view that is separate from folder numbers.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"027 timeline\"\n6:   - \"027 newest phase\"\n7:   - \"027 most recent spec folder\"\n8:   - \"027 chronological order\"\n9:   - \"which 027 phase is newest\"\n10: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n11: contextType: \"general\"\n12: _memory:\n13:   continuity:\n14:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\n15:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-14T07:20:50Z\"\n16:     recent_action: \"Regenerated chronological timeline from git history\"\n17:     next_safe_action: \"Use this file to find the most recent / oldest spec folder\"\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19: ---\n20: # 027 Chronological Timeline\n21: \n22: <!-- GENERATED FILE — do not hand-edit. Regenerate: `python3 scratch/gen-timeline.py > timeline.md` (run from the 027 root). -->\n23: \n24: > **Generated:** 2026-06-14T07:20:50Z — regenerate before relying on intra-day ordering; same-day commits made\n25: > after this stamp are not reflected until the next run.\n26: > **Sort key:** git last-commit timestamp touching each folder subtree, **newest → oldest** (the\n27: > recency view), taken from one atomic `git log` snapshot. The last-active column shows\n28: > `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` (committer local offset) because most folders share one commit day — the time\n29: > is what orders them. The `born` column is the folder's recorded `created_at` (or first git commit\n30: > of its `spec.md`), shown at day granularity.\n31: >\n32: > **Folder numbers are NOT chronology.** Numbers (`000`–`007`, child `NNN-`) encode topical/structural\n33: > identity assigned across reorg waves. This file is the *only* surface that orders by when work happened.\n34: > Phase identity → home mapping lives in [`context-index.md`](./context-index.md); the live track map lives\n35: > in [`spec.md`](./spec.md).\n36: >\n37: > **Changelog links:** §D maps every live spec folder to its packet changelog(s). Folders with none\n38: > (docs-only, research, or work consolidated into a parent rollup) show `(none)`. Phase parents link\n39: > their `-root.md` rollup, which indexes the child phase changelogs.\n40: >\n\n(Showing lines 1-40 of 438. Use offset=41 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Chronological Timeline [system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline]\"\ndescription: \"GENERATED chronological index of 027 live-tree spec folders, newest to oldest by git activity. The recency view that is separate from folder numbers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"027 timeline\"\n  - \"027 newest phase\"\n  - \"027 most recent spec folder\"\n  - \"027 chronological order\"\n  - \"which 027 phase is newest\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-14T07:20:50Z\"\n    recent_action: \"Regenerated chronological timeline from git history\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Use this file to find the most recent / oldest spec folder\"\n    completion_pct: 100\n---\n# 027 Chronological Timeline","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Chronological Timeline [system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline]\"\ndescription: \"GENERATED chronological index of 027 live-tree spec folders, newest to oldest by git activity. The recency view that is separate from folder numbers.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"027 timeline\"\n  - \"027 newest phase\"\n  - \"027 most recent spec folder\"\n  - \"027 chronological order\"\n  - \"which 027 phase is newest\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-14T07:20:50Z\"\n    recent_action: \"Regenerated chronological timeline from git history\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Use this file to find the most recent / oldest spec folder\"\n    completion_pct: 100\n---\n# 027 Chronological Timeline\n\n<!-- GENERATED FILE — do not hand-edit. Regenerate: `python3 scratch/gen-timeline.py > timeline.md` (run from the 027 root). -->\n\n> **Generated:** 2026-06-14T07:20:50Z — regenerate before relying on intra-day ordering; same-day commits made\n> after this stamp are not reflected until the next run.\n> **Sort key:** git last-commit timestamp touching each folder subtree, **newest → oldest** (the\n> recency view), taken from one atomic `git log` snapshot. The last-active column shows\n> `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` (committer local offset) because most folders share one commit day — the time\n> is what orders them. The `born` column is the folder's recorded `created_at` (or first git commit\n> of its `spec.md`), shown at day granularity.\n>\n> **Folder numbers are NOT chronology.** Numbers (`000`–`007`, child `NNN-`) encode topical/structural\n> identity assigned across reorg waves. This file is the *only* surface that orders by when work happened.\n> Phase identity → home mapping lives in [`context-index.md`](./context-index.md); the live track map lives\n> in [`spec.md`](./spec.md).\n>\n> **Changelog links:** §D maps every live spec folder to its packet changelog(s). Folders with none\n> (docs-only, research, or work consolidated into a parent rollup) show `(none)`. Phase parents link\n> their `-root.md` rollup, which indexes the child phase changelogs.\n>","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":40,"totalLines":438,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/timeline.md","time":{"start":1781422970899,"end":1781422970911}},"id":"prt_ec5155810001TMgNjgkrRfxark","sessionID":"ses_13aef63ccffel7tpaI1Dzxs3uq","messageID":"msg_ec5153c94001r4D9H3v7x9uYBQ"}}
